observations.recommendation:
We recommended that the LCE: 

Enforce a centralized system on the procurement of supplies, materials and equipment for proper control on the acquisition and issuances thereof wherein the GSO/Municipal Treasurer will determine the items to be procured based on the Consolidated Annual Procurement Plan of the Municipality and require the BAC to conduct a public bidding for items not available in the Procurement Service-DBM; 

Require the Office of the GSO/Municipal Treasurer to take charge on the preparation of voucher, purchase request, purchase order and other supporting documents pertaining to the procurement of supplies, materials and equipment;

Adhere strictly with the Letter of Instructions No. 755, Executive Order Nos. 289 series of 1987, 359 series of 1989, and 322 series of 2000, using the Electronic Procurement System by procuring commonly used supplies, materials and equipment from the Procurement Service (PS) DBM; 

Require the GSO/Municipal Treasurer to submit the Acceptance and Inspection Report of all consumables to the Auditor within twenty-four (24) hours from delivery; and

Require the Municipal Accountant to record purchases of supplies and materials to be carried in stock as inventory regardless of whether or not they were consumed within the accounting period following the perpetual inventory method.

